critical_positive:
We basically connected into areas like the stock market and how the mark fluctuates from now until election day.  We both agreed that things won't be really "normal" until sometime 2021.  
It was critical that I did not discuss my political affiliation with the other person to be basically polarizing myself in an area I tried not to bring politics but the political process from now until 11/3.
critical_negative:
I could hear myself in the background of his audio and it sounded like it was a bit distorted.  I wanted to ensure he was understanding what I was saying and commenting on was clear from my end.  
at certain points, we were speaking over each other but I did not know if it was from our video connections.

begin_memory_text: We introduced each other talked about prolific and other paid survey sites. We talked about how this survey works.
middle_memory_text: The conversation picked up. We talked about spending money, what we do for leisure. We talked about where we live and what its like where we live.
end_memory_text: Pretty good we were talking a lot about things we had in common but the end was approaching so I had to bring up the topic as time is money.
rest_of_day_open: I see it going great. I have plans ahead and means to achieve them. When problems arise I will equally rise to the occasion and I will overcome the obstacles in front of me such as I have done before in life. Why? Because I am Jack. I am great.
critical_positive: What worked well is what we had in common. Two bros talking about life during the pandemic. Times are weird for everyone but there is usually a common thread for someone in any conversation. My ability to steer the conversation towards things we had in common helped a lot I think.
critical_negative: What didn't work out was my humor. It is pretty hard to judge facial expressions and sarcasm in a zoom type setting. That is something I am learning to adjust to. This is good practice for zoom socializing. Which is why I try to make the most out of these situations. We had difficulty trying not to speak over each other.
